---
import Layout from "@/layouts/Layout.astro";
import Header from "@/components/Header.astro";
import Footer from "@/components/Footer.astro";

// 🛡️ 防呆处理
let baseUrl = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
if (!baseUrl.endsWith('/')) baseUrl += '/';
---

<Layout title="Privacy Policy" lang="en">
  <div class="page-wrapper">
    <Header />
    <div class="container markdown-content">
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="last-updated"><strong>Last Updated:</strong> June 16, 2026</p>

      <p>
        This Privacy Policy describes how SSH Config Manager ("we", "our", or
        "the software") handles your information. We are committed to protecting
        your privacy and ensuring the security of your data.
      </p>

      <h2>1. Data Collection and Usage</h2>

      <h3>1.1 No Data Collection</h3>
      <p>
        SSH Config Manager does <strong>not</strong> collect, transmit, or share any
        personal information, usage data, or telemetry. Specifically:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>No advertisements</strong> - The software contains no ads or ad
          trackers
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>No analytics</strong> - We do not collect analytics, crash reports,
          or usage statistics
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>No tracking</strong> - There are no tracking mechanisms, cookies,
          or user behavior monitoring
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>No data transmission</strong> - The software does not send any data
          to external servers during normal operation
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h3>1.2 Fully Offline Operation</h3>
      <p>
        The software is designed to operate completely offline. Both the trial
        version and the activated version can function without any internet
        connection. Activation itself can be completed offline by manually
        transferring the activation file from another internet-connected
        environment.
      </p>

      <h2>2. SSH Configuration Data</h2>

      <h3>2.1 Local Storage Only</h3>
      <p>
        All SSH configuration data is stored <strong
          >exclusively on your local device</strong
        > in a location of your choosing. This data never leaves your device and is
        never uploaded to any server or third-party service.
      </p>

      <h3>2.2 Your Responsibility</h3>
      <p>
        You maintain full control and responsibility for your SSH configuration
        data. We recommend maintaining regular backups of your configuration
        files.
      </p>

      <h2>3. Activation and Licensing</h2>

      <h3>3.1 Device Fingerprint</h3>
      <p>
        To verify and enforce license validity, the software generates a device
        fingerprint that is bound to your activation key. This fingerprint is
        generated locally on your device and is only transmitted during the
        activation process if you choose to use online activation.
      </p>

      <h3>3.2 Activation Data</h3>
      <p>
        When you activate the software (whether online or offline), the
        following information may be processed:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Device fingerprint (hardware-based identifier)</li>
        <li>License key</li>
        <li>Activation status</li>
      </ul>
      <p>This information is used solely for license validation purposes.</p>

      <h3>3.3 Data Deletion Rights</h3>
      <p>You have the right to request:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>License unbinding:</strong> Contact us via email to unbind your
          license from a device, allowing activation on a different device
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Complete data deletion:</strong> Request the complete deletion of
          all your personal activation-related data from our records
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        To exercise these rights, please contact us at <a
          data-email
          data-email-text></a>.
      </p>

      <h2>4. Third-Party Services</h2>
      <p>
        SSH Config Manager does not integrate with or rely on any third-party
        services, APIs, or libraries that collect user data. The software
        operates independently on your device.
      </p>

      <h2>5. Children's Privacy</h2>
      <p>
        Our software is not directed to children under the age of 13, and we do
        not knowingly collect personal information from children.
      </p>

      <h2>6. Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
      <p>
        We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify
        users of any material changes by updating the "Last Updated" date at the
        top of this policy. Continued use of the software after changes
        constitutes acceptance of the updated policy.
      </p>

      <h2>7. Contact Us</h2>
      <p>
        If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy or wish to exercise
        your data rights, please contact us at:
      </p>
      <p><a data-email data-email-text></a></p>

      <a href={baseUrl} class="back-link" style="display: inline-block; margin-bottom: 24px; color: #667eea; text-decoration: none; font-weight: 500;">← Back to Home</a>

      <div class="footer">
        <p>SSH Config Manager</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <Footer />
  </div>
</Layout>
